Class JointValues

java.lang.Object
  JointValues

public class JointValues
extends java.lang.Object

This class can store a set of joint values for the UMI-RTX robot. This robot has 6 degrees of freedom plus a gripper. The 6 joints representing those 6 degrees of freedom are the zed, shoulder, elbow, yaw, pitch and roll. The zed, shoulder and elbow are more related to the arm, while the yaw, pitch and roll are related to the hand. The gripper can be also be open or closed and is considered part of the joint representation.

This class also includes methods for converting the joint values to a string and for checking if another joint value is equal to the one stored in the class.
